It looks like setting USERID_HEADER and USERID_PREFIX environment variables to the empty string disable identity awareness; it doesn't fall back to GCP config. Here is where the values get ovewritten by environment variables
kubeflow/components/centraldashboard/app/server.ts
Line 31 in 06b4cb4
} = process.env;
And here is where the code ignores things if its the empty string.
kubeflow/components/centraldashboard/app/attach_user_middleware.ts
Line 12 in 06b4cb4
if (userIdHeader && req.header(userIdHeader)) {
So the solution is to override the USERID_HEADER and PREFIX values in kfctl_gcp_iap.0.6.2.yaml
